36:42.248 --> 36:44.080
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

37:13.956 --> 37:15.788
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

37:25.164 --> 37:26.372
(ZIP OPENS)

37:26.456 --> 37:27.956
(KEYS JINGLING)

40:20.330 --> 40:22.330
(FAINT CREAKING)

40:26.082 --> 40:28.206
(FAINT RUSTLING)

40:41.790 --> 40:43.706
(CREAKING)

40:45.082 --> 40:47.082
(MUFFLED RUMBLING)

40:54.958 --> 40:57.706
- (DOOR OPENS)
- (BOYS CHATTERING IN FRENCH)

41:02.706 --> 41:03.914
(SOLOMON EXCLAIMS)

41:07.830 --> 41:09.038
(BOYS KISSING)

41:14.458 --> 41:16.458
(BOYS WHISPERING AND SNIGGERING)

41:21.790 --> 41:22.998
(BOYS KISSING)

41:25.666 --> 41:27.498
(BOYS GIGGLING)

41:35.998 --> 41:37.830
(BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

41:51.874 --> 41:53.706
(DOOR OPENS QUIETLY)

41:59.330 --> 42:00.414
(SIGHS)

42:08.082 --> 42:09.746
What were you doing in my house?

42:11.706 --> 42:13.330
I left... I left my bag.

42:13.414 --> 42:15.038
And I just popped back
to get it.

42:15.538 --> 42:16.666
Why did you run?

42:16.746 --> 42:18.998
Because... you scared me.

42:23.374 --> 42:25.538
- What were you doing upstairs?
- I...

42:25.622 --> 42:26.622
Were you watching?

42:26.998 --> 42:28.206
Of course not.

42:29.330 --> 42:30.582
I left my bag.

42:31.038 --> 42:32.414
And, erm...

42:32.498 --> 42:34.038
I told your mum I was coming.

42:34.122 --> 42:35.746
She gave me the keys.

42:37.582 --> 42:38.830
You can ask her.

42:45.746 --> 42:47.166
I didn't mean to intrude.

42:48.330 --> 42:50.374
And I'm not gonna say anything.

43:00.414 --> 43:02.414
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

43:04.166 --> 43:05.998
(MOBILE RINGING)

43:22.914 --> 43:24.122
(RINGING STOPS)

43:36.998 --> 43:39.122
AUTOMATED VOICE: (ON MOBILE)
You have one saved message.

43:39.998 --> 43:41.458
AHMED: Well, it's four o'clock,

43:41.538 --> 43:43.330
which means
you're probably on your spot

43:43.414 --> 43:45.666
waving at me
like a mad woman. (CHUCKLES)

43:46.914 --> 43:48.790
Don't get too close
to that edge.

43:48.874 --> 43:51.206
I don't want you
getting blown off.

43:51.914 --> 43:53.746
We're making our way back
across now.

43:54.290 --> 43:56.290
I just thought
I'd call to see how you are.

43:57.374 --> 43:59.874
Anyway, er,I should be home normal time.

44:00.874 --> 44:02.082
See you later, love.

44:02.830 --> 44:04.666
(WATER DRIPPING)

44:20.454 --> 44:21.706
(MUFFLED CHATTER)

44:23.454 --> 44:25.082
GENEVIÈVE: Ahmed,
what's going on?

44:26.330 --> 44:28.454
Why haven't you been in touch?

44:29.330 --> 44:32.250
I have been doing this
all by myself.

44:32.330 --> 44:35.122
The least you could do
is get back to me, okay?

44:57.166 --> 44:58.666
(MOBILE CHIMES)

45:02.998 --> 45:04.538
- (MUFFLED THUD)
- (GENEVIÈVE GROANS)

45:08.498 --> 45:10.082
(GENEVIÈVE YELLS INDISTINCTLY)

45:12.582 --> 45:14.414
- (MOBILE CHIMES)
- (SOLOMON SIGHS)

45:15.622 --> 45:18.166
You know, when I was young,
we used to write letters.

45:19.666 --> 45:21.874
My husband and I were
a secret too.

45:22.498 --> 45:23.582
For years.

45:24.122 --> 45:25.874
Before his family found out.

45:26.998 --> 45:28.998
Must have been a bit younger
than you.

45:29.082 --> 45:30.414
(KEYPAD CLACKING)

45:30.498 --> 45:32.622
About 14 when we got together.

45:32.998 --> 45:34.206
Every summer,

45:35.830 --> 45:38.790
he'd go to his family's village
in Pakistan.

45:38.874 --> 45:40.706
Well, I couldn't write
to him there.

45:41.538 --> 45:42.582
So...

45:43.790 --> 45:47.290
we agreed that we'd look at the
moon at the same time every night.

45:48.874 --> 45:50.998
- (MOBILE CHIMES)
- (CHUCKLES)

45:52.414 --> 45:54.538
He made
these cassette tapes for me.

45:56.374 --> 45:59.830
So I'd listen to those.
That's how we saw each other.

46:00.914 --> 46:02.538
And what if there were no moon?

46:03.790 --> 46:05.914
Well, I guess we didn't see
each other that night.

46:07.206 --> 46:08.414
But I'd hear him.

46:14.582 --> 46:16.206
Have you ever been to the UK?

46:17.374 --> 46:18.746
Yeah, once.

46:18.830 --> 46:19.914
With your dad?

46:21.538 --> 46:22.746
Where'd you go?

46:23.330 --> 46:24.414
Dover Castle.

46:25.166 --> 46:26.998
(CHUCKLES) Dover Castle.

46:27.666 --> 46:29.414
Was that on a school trip?

46:30.330 --> 46:31.414
Yes.

46:32.498 --> 46:35.038
But I ran away from the group
to find my dad.

46:35.914 --> 46:36.914
Why?

46:39.038 --> 46:41.038
I guess I wanted to see
where he works.

46:41.954 --> 46:43.166
Did you find him?

46:44.790 --> 46:45.790
No.

46:47.082 --> 46:48.290
I got lost.

46:48.374 --> 46:49.790
The police found me.

46:51.082 --> 46:52.290
When was that then?

46:53.622 --> 46:54.998
A few years ago.

46:58.746 --> 47:00.250
Dad was really angry.

47:03.374 --> 47:04.582
Well, he was...

47:05.666 --> 47:08.746
He was probably just worried that
something might happen to you.

47:11.250 --> 47:12.666
Parents are like that.

47:35.666 --> 47:37.666
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)
- (SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

47:42.746 --> 47:44.622
(MOBILE RINGING)

47:44.706 --> 47:46.330
(SHIP HORN BLOWS)

48:05.250 --> 48:07.122
(MOBILE CONTINUES RINGING)

48:18.998 --> 48:21.122
(IN ENGLISH) So much crap,
I can't believe it.

48:33.954 --> 48:35.038
Mary?

48:37.206 --> 48:38.498
That's nice.

48:44.706 --> 48:45.954
Thank you.

48:48.122 --> 48:49.622
- Sol?
- (DOOR SLAMS)

48:49.706 --> 48:50.790
Sol!

48:54.538 --> 48:55.622
Sol?

49:45.746 --> 49:46.830
SOLOMON: Move!

49:50.250 --> 49:52.374
(DOOR OPENS, SHUTS)

50:08.790 --> 50:10.622
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

50:23.746 --> 50:25.374
Is Solomon okay?

50:27.998 --> 50:31.330
He wants to go
and live with his father.

50:34.746 --> 50:35.954
He hates me.

50:36.662 --> 50:38.082
I knew this would happen.

50:39.082 --> 50:40.330
How do you mean?

50:43.122 --> 50:45.746
Ahmed and I,
we are not married. He...

50:46.414 --> 50:48.250
He has a wife in the UK.

50:52.706 --> 50:55.498
Oh, so you've...
you've always known that...

50:55.582 --> 50:56.746
he was married?

50:57.538 --> 51:00.454
Ahmed doesn't have
a glass ceiling above his bed,

51:00.538 --> 51:03.082
so why should there be one
above my own?

51:03.662 --> 51:05.162
And does Solomon know
about this?

51:05.874 --> 51:07.706
No, he doesn't know anything.

51:08.498 --> 51:09.790
This is a problem.

51:12.206 --> 51:13.538
We're not married.

51:13.914 --> 51:15.454
We're not divorced.

51:16.330 --> 51:18.538
We are together
but also not together.

51:20.082 --> 51:22.662
He's hardly here
and then just pops up.

51:24.038 --> 51:26.162
No wonder the poor kid's
screwed up.

51:31.330 --> 51:32.414
Is he...

51:33.038 --> 51:34.874
Is he gonna leave her?

51:35.874 --> 51:36.954
For you?

51:37.038 --> 51:38.250
Oh. (LAUGHS)

51:38.330 --> 51:41.206
Husbands never leave the wife
for the other woman.

51:41.830 --> 51:45.038
If he was going to, he would
have done this years ago.

51:45.122 --> 51:47.038
But you're buying
a new house together.

51:47.122 --> 51:48.206
No, no, no.

51:48.290 --> 51:49.914
I'm buying it alone.

51:50.454 --> 51:52.954
I'm not sharing that too, so...

51:55.662 --> 51:57.582
This place
is all falling apart...

51:58.082 --> 51:59.914
I can't stand this any more.

52:07.122 --> 52:09.746
What does Ahmed say about...
about her?

52:11.374 --> 52:13.498
- Er, who? The wife?
- Mmm.

52:14.162 --> 52:15.250
Nothing.

52:15.954 --> 52:18.082
I forbade him to talk about her.

52:19.706 --> 52:21.874
- You're not curious?
- Of course.

52:23.330 --> 52:24.538
I'm human.

52:25.954 --> 52:27.162
Pakistani.

52:28.206 --> 52:29.290
No kids.

52:30.830 --> 52:32.954
- That can all stay over there.
- He said that?

52:33.038 --> 52:35.250
I've never seen a picture.
I don't care...

52:35.330 --> 52:36.790
- He said that?
- What?

52:36.874 --> 52:38.082
MARY: I mean...

52:38.830 --> 52:40.038
How... How can...

52:40.662 --> 52:42.082
How can you share?

52:42.954 --> 52:44.250
Knowingly?

52:46.538 --> 52:50.038
We all break the rules
we set for ourselves in the end.

52:54.830 --> 52:56.330
You must know him very well.

52:57.250 --> 52:59.998
Er... What I know is that...

53:00.830 --> 53:04.374
being with me has made him a
better husband for someone else.

53:05.998 --> 53:07.874
This is sad for me.

53:08.998 --> 53:10.414
But mostly for Solomon,

53:11.082 --> 53:13.706
that he's a disappointment
as a father.

53:30.416 --> 53:31.500
(SIGHS)

53:31.580 --> 53:33.456
(RAIN PATTERING)

54:21.832 --> 54:23.040
(SNIFFS)

54:38.664 --> 54:39.748
(SNIFFLES)

55:28.332 --> 55:29.416
(SNIFFLES)

55:35.000 --> 55:36.080
(SNIFFLING)

55:39.788 --> 55:42.416
(MOBILE VIBRATING)

55:46.456 --> 55:47.664
(GASPS SOFTLY)

55:49.832 --> 55:51.664
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

55:59.248 --> 56:01.080
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

56:31.916 --> 56:33.456
SOLOMON: (IN ENGLISH)
Whoa! Strike!

56:39.288 --> 56:41.040
(BIN LORRY DRIVES AWAY)

56:45.624 --> 56:46.708
(SIGHS)

56:47.080 --> 56:48.208
That's it.

56:50.872 --> 56:52.540
(SIGHS)
We're pretty much done now.

56:54.208 --> 56:55.288
MARY: Hmm.

56:55.956 --> 56:59.664
- What time are the movers coming
tomorrow? - Er, in the morning.

57:00.664 --> 57:03.040
Thank you, Mary,
for everything, really.

57:03.124 --> 57:07.288
You've been an amazing help. I
couldn't have done this without you.

57:07.372 --> 57:09.000
- Oh, no.
- Oh...

57:09.624 --> 57:11.248
We've got used to
having you around,

57:11.332 --> 57:14.248
so maybe you can come next week
once we're settled?

57:15.416 --> 57:17.916
Oh, I... Er... Erm...

57:18.956 --> 57:20.248
I need to check.

57:20.332 --> 57:22.788
Okay. Anyway,
you have my number.

57:23.288 --> 57:25.416
Okay? Just call me
when you want to.

57:25.496 --> 57:26.916
- See you soon.
- Mmm.

57:32.664 --> 57:34.080
(BOYS CHATTERING)

57:53.872 --> 57:55.332
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

58:08.040 --> 58:09.124
(DOOR CLOSES)

58:13.416 --> 58:14.624
Are you hungry?

58:17.248 --> 58:19.000
I could cook something.

58:19.456 --> 58:20.872
Well, it's all packed up.

58:22.916 --> 58:24.000
Yeah.

58:25.332 --> 58:27.164
I'm sure
we could find something.

59:08.664 --> 59:10.164
(SIZZLING)

59:30.000 --> 59:31.288
(SIZZLING)

59:47.124 --> 59:48.624
(BLOWING)

59:56.872 --> 59:59.000
- This is delicious.
- (CHUCKLES)

59:59.540 --> 1:00:01.664
- What's it called again?
- Saag.

1:00:02.540 --> 1:00:03.704
It's spinach.

1:00:03.788 --> 1:00:05.624
A bit DIY, I'm afraid.

1:00:06.456 --> 1:00:09.080
Though I am very impressed
with the tortilla wraps.

1:00:09.872 --> 1:00:12.288
Who knew they'd make
such a good substitute for roti?

1:00:13.040 --> 1:00:14.124
Mmm.

1:00:17.704 --> 1:00:19.124
You eat like my dad.

1:00:25.540 --> 1:00:26.748
Mmm, come on.

1:00:28.624 --> 1:00:29.832
Take a little piece.

1:00:30.916 --> 1:00:32.748
- All right.
- Mmm-hmm, like that.

1:00:33.204 --> 1:00:34.496
Just a little bit, then.

1:00:35.288 --> 1:00:36.540
Now you use your thumb.

1:00:36.916 --> 1:00:39.248
These two fingers. That's it.

1:00:39.332 --> 1:00:40.956
And you just scoop it.

1:00:42.704 --> 1:00:44.704
There, see now.
Look, you can hold it!

1:00:44.788 --> 1:00:46.164
(BOTH LAUGH)

1:00:47.832 --> 1:00:49.748
- ANTHONY: Mmm.
- (CHUCKLES)

1:00:50.496 --> 1:00:53.248
You're doing very well.
You just keep going.

1:00:57.540 --> 1:00:58.956
Did your dad, erm,

1:00:59.704 --> 1:01:02.204
ever teach you to speak Urdu?

1:01:02.288 --> 1:01:03.916
- Mmm-hmm.
- He did?

1:01:04.788 --> 1:01:07.288
But I understand it
more than I can speak.

1:01:07.372 --> 1:01:08.496
MARY: Oh.

1:01:18.496 --> 1:01:20.248
Erm, wait. Erm...

1:01:27.916 --> 1:01:29.288
My husband.

1:01:29.372 --> 1:01:32.456
I learnt because I wanted to know
what his family was saying about me.

1:01:32.540 --> 1:01:33.956
(SOLOMON LAUGHS)

1:01:46.704 --> 1:01:48.332
Hmm. Well...

1:01:49.372 --> 1:01:52.540
I have been
to Lahore and Karachi.

1:01:52.624 --> 1:01:53.704
Hmm.

1:01:54.624 --> 1:01:56.040
And then,
when I first got married,

1:01:56.124 --> 1:01:59.872
my husband, he took me to his home
village just outside Islamabad.

1:02:03.164 --> 1:02:04.540
I'd like to go one day.

1:02:04.624 --> 1:02:06.124
(DOOR OPENS)

1:02:10.540 --> 1:02:11.748
(DOOR CLOSES)

1:02:18.872 --> 1:02:20.788
Mary, you... You're still here.

1:02:21.540 --> 1:02:22.832
Yes, erm...

1:02:23.456 --> 1:02:26.204
He was hungry.
And I had a free evening.

1:02:27.288 --> 1:02:28.496
I didn't mind.

1:02:31.164 --> 1:02:32.456
Did you cook this?

1:02:32.832 --> 1:02:33.832
Yes.

1:02:35.872 --> 1:02:37.164
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

1:02:37.788 --> 1:02:40.204
I should have
stayed in, after all.

1:02:53.416 --> 1:02:54.624
May I join you?

1:02:54.704 --> 1:02:57.332
Oh, would you...
Would you like some yourself?

1:02:57.416 --> 1:02:58.496
No, no.

1:02:58.956 --> 1:03:01.164
I've eaten. Thank you.

1:03:05.832 --> 1:03:07.456
(POURING WINE)

1:03:23.000 --> 1:03:25.204
Did he say
where he's been all this time?

1:03:25.288 --> 1:03:28.704
He hasn't picked up my calls.
And I'm worried.

1:03:37.040 --> 1:03:39.456
(GENEVIÈVE LAUGHING)

1:03:46.664 --> 1:03:48.496
Why are you
criticising her food?

1:03:49.248 --> 1:03:50.664
She's right in front of you.

1:03:55.872 --> 1:03:57.080
Do you feel inferior?

1:03:57.704 --> 1:04:00.540
- Because I said her cooking
was good. - Don't be stupid.

1:04:01.124 --> 1:04:02.956
She's done me a favour
feeding you.

1:04:10.416 --> 1:04:12.540
I can't wait for
my father to arrive tomorrow.

1:04:13.000 --> 1:04:16.124
GENEVIÈVE: Oh, we're gonna have a
discussion, the three of us, for sure.

1:04:24.540 --> 1:04:25.624
Nice.

1:04:26.540 --> 1:04:28.288
Now I'm a little bastard.

1:04:28.372 --> 1:04:30.540
I can hardly accuse her
of being a liar on that.

1:04:41.080 --> 1:04:42.164
- (SPITS)
- (GASPS)

1:04:47.624 --> 1:04:49.040
(GASPS)

1:04:56.000 --> 1:04:58.124
(DOOR OPENS, SLAMS SHUT)

1:04:59.788 --> 1:05:01.916
(MARY BREATHING SHAKILY)

1:05:15.872 --> 1:05:17.788
Who do you think you are?

1:05:22.832 --> 1:05:25.040
Don't you ever touch my son.

1:05:35.496 --> 1:05:37.496
(BREATH SHUDDERING)

