Your saved message has expired.

1:06:06.748 --> 1:06:08.456
You've reached voicemail.

1:06:08.540 --> 1:06:10.748
Press 1 for new messages.

1:06:10.832 --> 1:06:13.456
Press 2 for saved messages.

1:06:16.204 --> 1:06:17.704
(SHOWER RUNNING)

1:06:25.288 --> 1:06:27.288
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

1:06:45.372 --> 1:06:47.248
(SEAGULLS CALLING)

1:07:53.456 --> 1:07:55.540
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1:08:07.456 --> 1:08:09.288
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

1:08:21.456 --> 1:08:22.956
(LORRY DOORS CLOSING)

1:08:28.080 --> 1:08:29.916
(LORRY DRIVING AWAY)

1:08:38.788 --> 1:08:39.956
(MARY GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1:08:44.916 --> 1:08:46.456
I'm Ahmed's wife.

1:08:51.332 --> 1:08:52.580
I'm his wife.

1:08:58.288 --> 1:08:59.416
Fahima?

1:08:59.916 --> 1:09:01.208
It's my Muslim name.

1:09:04.624 --> 1:09:05.708
(CHUCKLES DRYLY)

1:09:07.372 --> 1:09:10.416
You're nothing
like what I imagined.

1:09:16.956 --> 1:09:18.500
Why did you come here?

1:09:20.500 --> 1:09:22.124
I found out about you.

1:09:22.832 --> 1:09:25.624
- And I... I wanted to...
- All this time,

1:09:26.416 --> 1:09:29.540
(VOICE BREAKING) you were
in my home, in my things.

1:09:30.288 --> 1:09:32.332
- Everything!
- Geneviève.

1:09:32.872 --> 1:09:34.372
I need you to listen.

1:09:34.456 --> 1:09:35.832
Where is Ahmed?

1:09:35.916 --> 1:09:38.872
I... I wanna say that
I had no idea about Solomon...

1:09:38.956 --> 1:09:40.916
But where is Ahmed?

1:09:43.164 --> 1:09:44.248
Huh?

1:09:45.872 --> 1:09:49.164
So you're the reason
he won't speak to me?

1:09:49.248 --> 1:09:50.956
I've been humiliated.

1:09:51.040 --> 1:09:52.872
You two-faced fucking bitch.

1:09:53.708 --> 1:09:54.832
Who are you?

1:09:54.916 --> 1:09:55.996
His wife.

1:09:56.080 --> 1:09:57.624
(BREATHING SHAKILY)
I'm his wife.

1:09:58.996 --> 1:10:00.208
I'm Ahmed's wife!

1:10:05.956 --> 1:10:08.124
- (IN ENGLISH) Solomon, I...
- GENEVIÈVE: Shut up! Shut up!

1:10:12.664 --> 1:10:13.916
He has a son.

1:10:14.832 --> 1:10:17.288
He has a responsibility.

1:10:18.164 --> 1:10:21.872
And I don't fucking care of
him, you, me or anything else,

1:10:21.956 --> 1:10:25.748
but he has a responsibility to our
son, and you can't take that away!

1:10:26.416 --> 1:10:27.500
He's dead.

1:10:33.872 --> 1:10:35.288
This is stupid.

1:10:39.956 --> 1:10:41.124
(SIGHS)

1:10:43.332 --> 1:10:45.332
(MOBILE RINGING)

1:10:58.664 --> 1:11:00.040
(IN ENGLISH)
Why do you have his phone?

1:11:03.664 --> 1:11:05.040
(SNIFFLES)

1:11:06.664 --> 1:11:09.372
- Solomon, I need...
- Don't touch him!

1:11:10.456 --> 1:11:12.664
You sick fucking woman.

1:11:13.540 --> 1:11:14.832
- Get out of here.
- I need...

1:11:14.916 --> 1:11:16.540
- Get out! Get out!
- Please. Please...

1:11:19.080 --> 1:11:20.748
- MARY: Listen to me...

1:11:20.832 --> 1:11:22.288
Get out! Bitch!

1:11:22.372 --> 1:11:24.788
- Listen...
- Get out! Get out!

1:11:31.040 --> 1:11:32.248
(SIGHS)

1:11:35.040 --> 1:11:36.456
(GASPING)

1:11:41.580 --> 1:11:42.788
(SOLOMON WHIMPERS)

1:11:47.748 --> 1:11:48.956
(SIGHS)

1:11:58.080 --> 1:11:59.164
(SNIFFLES)

1:12:01.456 --> 1:12:02.872
(SOLOMON CRYING)

1:12:31.456 --> 1:12:33.916
WEATHER REPORTER: ...rain at
times. Bit of sun around 2:00.

1:12:33.996 --> 1:12:35.748
The best of the weather by far

1:12:35.832 --> 1:12:38.872
is across Northern England,Scotland,and
Northern Ireland...

1:13:47.500 --> 1:13:49.832
ALL: Allahu Akbar.

1:13:50.956 --> 1:13:53.456
WOMAN 1: (IN ENGLISH) Are you
ready? WOMAN 2: Here we go.

1:13:55.540 --> 1:13:57.832
MAN 1: There you go. MAN 2:
Look at her, she's so good.

1:13:57.916 --> 1:13:59.416
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1:14:01.996 --> 1:14:03.500
FAROOQ: (IN ARABIC)
In the name of God.

1:14:10.372 --> 1:14:11.872
WOMAN: (IN ENGLISH)
She's so good.

1:14:18.164 --> 1:14:19.664
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1:14:21.164 --> 1:14:23.580
- (BABY FUSSES)
- (SOFT SHUSHING)

1:14:30.704 --> 1:14:31.956
(LAUGHTER)

1:14:32.664 --> 1:14:34.500
WOMAN:
Skinhead in the family now.

1:14:34.580 --> 1:14:36.080
(LAUGHTER)

1:14:37.456 --> 1:14:40.288
(INDISTINCT CHATTER
AND LAUGHTER)

1:14:41.996 --> 1:14:43.996
(CLOCK TICKING)

1:14:48.916 --> 1:14:50.416
(ENGINE IDLING)

1:14:55.372 --> 1:14:56.580
(ENGINE STOPS)

1:14:57.624 --> 1:14:58.788
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

1:15:04.372 --> 1:15:05.456
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

1:15:48.788 --> 1:15:49.916
(GASPS SOFTLY)

1:17:07.164 --> 1:17:08.664
(SNIFFS)

1:17:16.248 --> 1:17:17.704
(KISSES, SIGHS)

1:17:26.664 --> 1:17:28.664
- (WOOD CREAKING)
- (MUFFLED FOOTSTEPS)

1:18:22.288 --> 1:18:25.372
Why did Ahmed tell you
that I was Pakistani?

1:18:27.916 --> 1:18:29.124
I have no idea.

1:18:33.040 --> 1:18:35.540
You know, in all the time
I had with him,

1:18:38.164 --> 1:18:41.288
I never wondered what he might
look like as a young man.

1:18:45.204 --> 1:18:46.456
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

1:18:46.540 --> 1:18:47.624
I lied

1:18:48.040 --> 1:18:51.996
when I said I didn't want
to know about you. I did.

1:18:53.540 --> 1:18:55.664
But if I knew who you were,

1:18:57.040 --> 1:18:58.872
what you looked like...

1:19:01.124 --> 1:19:02.956
I would have gone mad.

1:19:08.664 --> 1:19:10.164
I was jealous of you.

1:19:11.164 --> 1:19:13.664
That he wouldn't leave you
for me.

1:19:18.872 --> 1:19:20.500
I convinced myself

1:19:21.832 --> 1:19:23.956
I was fine with sharing...

1:19:25.624 --> 1:19:29.040
because I always thought that
I had the better half of him.

1:19:42.456 --> 1:19:43.664
(SIGHS)

1:20:00.204 --> 1:20:02.040
(FOOTSTEPS DESCENDING)

1:20:05.996 --> 1:20:07.204
AHMED: Hi, Mary.

1:20:08.332 --> 1:20:09.956
I'm not sure
what day you'll get this,

1:20:10.040 --> 1:20:14.124
but today is Monday the
29thof August, 1974.

1:20:16.456 --> 1:20:18.332
It's 3:00 in the morning here,

1:20:18.412 --> 1:20:20.912
so I think it must be 10 o'clock
where you are?

1:20:23.664 --> 1:20:27.540
Everyone's sleeping in the courtyard
because it's so hot. (CHUCKLES)

1:20:30.912 --> 1:20:32.332
It smells amazing.

1:20:32.956 --> 1:20:35.164
All of the lemons
are coming out on the trees.

1:20:35.248 --> 1:20:37.248
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

1:20:38.288 --> 1:20:39.500
Can you hear that?

1:20:40.912 --> 1:20:42.080
It's crickets.

1:20:43.912 --> 1:20:44.996
Hey.

1:20:45.872 --> 1:20:47.704
If there's a full moon here,

1:20:47.788 --> 1:20:50.288
does that mean there's
a full moon where you are too?

1:20:53.500 --> 1:20:55.500
I wonder what you look like
right now.

1:20:57.832 --> 1:20:59.664
Oh, I think
the tape's running out.

1:21:02.624 --> 1:21:03.832
Keep looking up.

1:21:06.124 --> 1:21:07.996
Where did you find that?

1:21:08.080 --> 1:21:09.288
(RECORDER CLICKS OFF)

1:21:10.956 --> 1:21:12.500
It was... It was in the drawer.

1:21:40.500 --> 1:21:41.832
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

1:21:44.912 --> 1:21:46.080
(SNIFFLES)

1:21:48.664 --> 1:21:50.664
(BREATH SHUDDERING)

1:22:23.412 --> 1:22:24.832
(CRYING)

1:22:32.624 --> 1:22:34.748
(GASPING)

1:22:37.872 --> 1:22:39.704
(SOBBING)

1:22:59.956 --> 1:23:01.788
(BOTH CONTINUE CRYING)

1:23:13.704 --> 1:23:15.704
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

